description.displayText: I highly recommend Natela! She's dependable, punctual, thorough and works diligently and fast, all with a wonderful attitude. I hire her three times and she was a life saver each time. When I had to move she helped me organize all of my things into boxes, clean the apartment and then helped me organize everything into my place. Recently she helped me organize all of my clothes and assist with cleaning and organizing my dresser drawers and closets. She pays attention to detail and goes above and beyond anticipating what needs to be done. You will not be disappointed with Natela! She's a wonderful person and fabulous household assistant!

description.displayText: Natela helped with housekeeping every Friday about 2 months. She has no experience and doesn't know cleaning supplies. She cleaned okay. Natela teared pillow case and broke holder in the bathroom. She texted on Thursday after 10 PM that she is not coming on Friday morning. Then on Monday morning she sent to me picture from the airplane and message that she is leaving on the vacation for a long time.

description.displayText: Natela watched my daughter, G, for 7 months while we lived in downtown Chicago. Our family feels that Natela was an absolute blessing because she was not only an incredible nanny but a wonderful person. She is always punctual and willing to go above and beyond to meet G's needs. She worked with G daily on building independence and meeting developmental goals. Natela was always looking for new toys and activities to do with G to learn and be creative. Natela is also very intuitive to G's schedule. G looked forward to her time with Natela each day and would run to her stroller to get ready for her arrival. Any family would be lucky to have Natela caring for their children and we will be forever grateful to know her.
